<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="87">
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">Head</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Carinostigmus capiconvergens Bashir &amp; Ma, sp. nov. (A-C, F-I, L-P female D, E, J, K male) A, D head, frontal B, E head, dorsal C head, ventral F head, lateral G, J scutum, scutellum and metanotum, dorsal H propodeum, dorso-posterior I, K thorax, lateral L scutum anterior, dorsal M pygidial plate N petiole, lateral O petiole, dorsal P metasoma, dorsal. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.81.61892.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/513020" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">2A-C, F</figureCitation>
). Mandible tridentate apically; labrum pentagonal, gently round toward apex; clypeus nearly flat, with several coarse punctures medially; free margin of median lobe of clypeus narrowly produced, nearly truncate, with two small lateral teeth, lateral lobe with inconspicuous tooth (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Carinostigmus capiconvergens Bashir &amp; Ma, sp. nov. (A-C, F-I, L-P female D, E, J, K male) A, D head, frontal B, E head, dorsal C head, ventral F head, lateral G, J scutum, scutellum and metanotum, dorsal H propodeum, dorso-posterior I, K thorax, lateral L scutum anterior, dorsal M pygidial plate N petiole, lateral O petiole, dorsal P metasoma, dorsal. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.81.61892.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/513020" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">2A</figureCitation>
); setae on margin of clypeus and mandible long, longer than labrum length; median and lower frons coriaceous, dull, with broad, deep frontal median furrow, a sturdy frontal median longitudinal carina, inter-antennal tubercle shorter than midocellus diameter; upper frons with several fine punctures, longitudinal carina lacking (Fig. 
